DSSCs prepared using dyes $\mathbf{5 a} \mathbf{- b}$ show very similar photovoltaic efficiencies: $2.98 \%$ for $\mathbf{5 a}$ and $3.01 \%$ for $\mathbf{5 b}$. The slightly higher efficiency of the DSSC sensitized with $\mathbf{5 b}$ dye (about 33\% of the efficiency of the DSSC with N719 dye), bearing a bithiophene moiety as the $\pi$-spacer/auxiliary electron

